already a (in some cases an unwritten) convention.

I think it would improv=
e extensibility and visibility on the web: I can introduce new media types =
based on existing ones.

You can already base a media type on an existing o=
ne by documenting that in it&#39;s specification

Any client, e.g. a browser, b=
eing aware of the &quot;hierachical media type&quot; concept could render a &quot;applicat=
ion/contact+xhtml+xml&quot; as usual (if he has no clue what contact+html is) or=
 could do something useful with it. For example, providing the user a popup=
 with &quot;Do you want to add this contact to your address book?&quot;.

You don&#39;t n=
eed a media type identifier to do this, you should do it by standardising a=
 link relation e.g. rel=3D&quot;contact&quot;

Cheers,
Mike




